# E2E Scenario Documentation

`docs/e2e-scenarios.md` is the canonical catalogue of all Playwright E2E scenarios. It must always reflect the actual test files.

## When to update

Update `docs/e2e-scenarios.md` any time you:

- **Add** a new `test(...)` block to any `*.spec.ts` file
- **Remove** or **rename** an existing scenario
- **Add** a new spec file (`NN-name.spec.ts`)
- **Change** the user story a scenario belongs to

## What to update

1. **Header** — increment `Total scenarios` count.
2. **Scenario Index table** — add/remove/update the row. Assign the next sequential ID (`E34`, `E35`, …).
3. **User Story section** — add/remove/update the row in the matching `## USN` section.
4. **New user story** — if adding a new spec file for a new user story, add a new `## USN — ...` section.

## Example: adding scenario E34

```markdown
<!-- Scenario Index -->
| E34 | 07-new-feature | US7 | User can export report as CSV | functional |

<!-- US7 section -->
| E34 | User can export report as CSV | Export button triggers download, file name matches `report-*.csv` |
```

## Do not skip this step

The document is read by the team to understand test coverage at a glance. An out-of-date catalogue is worse than no catalogue.
